The paper proposes a graphical representation of preferences and search algorithms for dominance testing based on this representation. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories, as it deals with automated decision tools. The paper also mentions network topologies, which suggests that it may belong to the Data Structures (cs.DS) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses algorithms, which suggests that it may also belong to the Computational Complexity (cs.CC) sub-category.
